A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Launch, Expose, Advise, Direct Center for Youth; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, founded in 2007 by Atlanta native and former Chicago Clubs outfielder C.J.
4 Stewart and his wife, Kelli, the Launch, Expose, Advise, Direct (L.E.A.D) Center for Youth
5 aims to empower Atlanta's Black youth through the methodology of sports-based youth
6 development; and
7 WHEREAS, L.E.A.D. helps participants build sustainable, meaningful lives and break
8 inter-generational cycles of poverty and trauma by using sports to foster leadership, civic
9 engagement, and community service; and
10 WHEREAS, through direct service programming, L.E.A.D. uses baseball for boys and tennis
11 for girls to equip students in Atlanta Public Schools and metro Atlanta with the confidence
12 and skills needed to overcome crime, poverty, and racism; and
13 WHEREAS, L.E.A.D. bridges a critical gap for vulnerable families in inner-city Atlanta by
14 offering high quality sports-based youth development programs that are paid for by the
